-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
PLACEHOLDER — REPLACE WITH YOUR AWS SIGNER CODE-SIGNING CERTIFICATE (PUBLIC).

This is the PUBLIC code-signing certificate (ECDSA P-256) whose private key the
AWS Signer profile uses to sign OTA images. The OTA PAL verifies each downloaded
image's "sig-sha256-ecdsa" signature against this cert before activating it.

Generate it with aws-iot/scripts/make-codesign-cert.sh and copy ecdsasigner.crt
here. This one is public (not a secret), but it MUST match the Signer profile
you push OTA updates with, or signature verification fails and the job is
rejected.
-----END CERTIFICATE-----
